    <h1 class="heading1">Pain Management Department at Aatura Hospital</h1>
    <h4 class="heading4">At Aatura Hospital, our Pain Management Department is dedicated to helping patients find relief from acute and chronic pain conditions. Led by a team of skilled pain management specialists, we offer comprehensive evaluations, personalized treatment plans, and advanced interventional procedures to address a wide range of pain conditions and improve patients' quality of life.</h4>

    <div class="content1">
        <div class="content-left">
            <h3>Our Services</h3>
            <h4>Comprehensive Pain Assessment</h4>
            <p>Our pain management specialists conduct thorough assessments to identify the underlying causes of pain and develop personalized treatment plans tailored to each patient's unique needs. We take into account medical history, diagnostic imaging, and physical examinations to formulate an accurate diagnosis and effective treatment approach.</p>

            <h4>Medication Management</h4>
            <p>We offer medication management services to help patients manage their pain effectively while minimizing side effects and risks. Our pain specialists prescribe appropriate medications, such as nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs), opioids, muscle relaxants, antidepressants, and anticonvulsants, as part of a comprehensive treatment plan.</p>

            <h4>Interventional Pain Procedures</h4>
            <p>We perform a variety of minimally invasive interventional procedures to alleviate pain and improve function for patients with chronic pain conditions. These procedures may include epidural steroid injections, nerve blocks, facet joint injections, radiofrequency ablation, spinal cord stimulation, and intrathecal drug delivery systems.</p>

            <h4>Physical Therapy and Rehabilitation</h4>
            <p>Our Pain Management Department collaborates with physical therapists and rehabilitation specialists to offer comprehensive rehabilitation programs for patients with chronic pain conditions. These programs may include therapeutic exercises, manual therapy techniques, modalities such as heat and cold therapy, and patient education to promote healing, restore function, and improve quality of life.</p>

            <h4>Alternative and Complementary Therapies</h4>
            <p>In addition to traditional pain management approaches, we offer alternative and complementary therapies to help patients manage their pain and improve overall well-being. These may include acupuncture, chiropractic care, massage therapy, mindfulness-based stress reduction, and biofeedback techniques, tailored to each patient's preferences and needs.</p>

            <h4>Psychological Support and Counseling</h4>
            <p>Chronic pain can have a significant impact on patients' emotional well-being and quality of life. Our Pain Management Department provides psychological support and counseling services to help patients cope with the psychological and emotional aspects of living with chronic pain. We offer individual counseling, support groups, cognitive-behavioral therapy (CBT), relaxation techniques, and stress management strategies to promote psychological resilience and improve coping skills.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-right"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="content2">
